From: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
Subject: [PATCH 1/8] hw/display: add apple-gfx-pci-linux port skeleton

Introduce two new source files and one header that provide
the scaffolding for a Linux C port of `hw/display/apple-gfx-pci.m`
and the common logic from `hw/display/apple-gfx.m`:

  * `hw/display/apple-gfx-linux.h` - state struct, callback
    prototypes, task-list bookkeeping.
  * `hw/display/apple-gfx-pci-linux.c` - PCI device type
    registration and minimal instance_init.
  * `hw/display/apple-gfx-common-linux.c` - stub entry
    points for the shell callbacks the library will call.

No meson/Kconfig wiring yet; that arrives in patch 7. The
files are not buildable at this point; subsequent patches
fill in the behaviour step by step so the series is
bisectable at a per-feature level.

The port targets `libapplegfx-vulkan` as the backend (found
via pkg-config); the library reimplements the PGDevice /
PGShellCallbacks surface of Apple's
ParavirtualizedGraphics.framework on top of Mesa lavapipe.
The guest-side `AppleParavirtGPU.kext` is unchanged.

Signed-off-by: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
